The areas <u>of $X, Y$ and $Z$ are given, $$\pi(R_0^2 - R_1^2),\pi(R_1^2 - R_2^2) $$and $$ \pi\left(\frac{(2R_0 - 1)^2 - (R_2 - 2)^2}{4}\right),$$ where $R_0$ represents the radius of the outer circle, $R_1$ represents the radius of the middle one and figure Z is the innermost circle respectively.
</think> \ <answer>For $X,$ the area is \begin{align*}
\pi(7^2 - 6^2) &= \pi(49 - 36) \\
&= 13\pi
\end{align*}and the radius being 7, the area of the regular polygon is \begin{align*}
\frac{1}{2}(7)(7)(\sin\frac{\pi}{3}) &= \frac{49\sqrt{3}}{4}
\end{align*}The area of the individual region is then \begin{align*}
\frac{49\sqrt{3}}{4} - \pi(6^2 - 4^2) &= \frac{49\sqrt{3}}{4} - 20\pi
\end{align*}

For $Z,$ the area \begin{align*}
\pi(4^2 - \left(\frac{7 - 4}{2}\right)^2) 
&= \pi \left( 16 - \frac{9}{4} \right) 
&= \frac{64\pi - 9\pi}{4}
\end{align*}

Then the areas of the other region, Y, is \begin{align*}
\frac{64\pi - 9\pi}{4} - \frac{49\sqrt{3}}{4}
&= \frac{55\pi - 49\sqrt{3}}{4}.
\end{align*}Then the difference between the largest and smallest areas is $$\frac{64\pi \boxed{- 9\pi +49\sqrt{3}}}{4} \cdot \frac{4}{4} =  \frac{55\pi - 49\sqrt{3}}{4}.$$
</answer>

